Get changed.

4
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:01,960
It's ready.

5
00:03:02,559 --> 00:03:04,440
Go over there.

6
00:03:18,919 --> 00:03:20,399
Hold it.

7
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:47,039
-Who chose this place?
-Me. Don't you like it?

8
00:03:49,720 --> 00:03:52,119
It's lovely. Thanks.

9
00:03:52,320 --> 00:03:58,160
-What's he saying?
-It's a good spot for a sniper.

10
00:03:59,759 --> 00:04:04,000
-Should I leave the glasses here?
-Yes.

11
00:04:23,359 --> 00:04:27,880
Sit here until we've gone over the hill.

12
00:04:28,959 --> 00:04:33,398
-If you take the gun, he'll shoot you.
-I don't shoot in the back.

13
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:37,519
They all say that, but Iast week
Big Jussi got a bullet here.

14
00:04:40,678 --> 00:04:44,678
Good luck, private. Goodbye.

15
00:05:57,880 --> 00:05:59,519
Damn!

16
00:10:41,718 --> 00:10:45,039
<i>Down by the hill, you see?</i>

17
00:10:45,239 --> 00:10:48,598
<i>I see. Then where?</i>

18
00:10:49,799 --> 00:10:57,598
One turn to the left, 2nd to the right, 3rd
past the burned bridge, there's a ford....

19
00:10:57,799 --> 00:11:02,278
I believe you're innocent. You're
a good man and an honest officer.

20
00:11:02,479 --> 00:11:04,158
Stop babbling!

21
00:11:04,299 --> 00:11:07,336
Comrade lieutenant,
for your journey!

22
00:11:07,501 --> 00:11:09,303
Let's go!

23
00:11:12,205 --> 00:11:14,707
Good luck, comrade lieutenant!

24
00:11:28,151 --> 00:11:29,253
Careful!

25
00:11:29,420 --> 00:11:32,723
Comrade lieutenant,
you can see the state of the road!

26
00:11:42,564 --> 00:11:45,400
Comrades, give us a push!

27
00:11:55,842 --> 00:11:57,411
Mister!

28
00:11:57,744 --> 00:11:58,910
Mister!

29
00:11:59,079 --> 00:12:03,548
I recognized you!
You worked at our shooting range.

30
00:12:03,715 --> 00:12:04,949
What shooting range?

31
00:12:05,116 --> 00:12:07,051
By the market.

32
00:12:07,219 --> 00:12:08,819
What market?

33
00:12:08,987 --> 00:12:11,221
In Bezhetsk. Near the market.

34
00:12:11,389 --> 00:12:12,623
No, it wasn't me.

35
00:12:12,789 --> 00:12:16,693
You look like him, but you used
to have a moustache.

36
00:12:16,860 --> 00:12:20,329
-Stop talking to the prisoner!
-Get lost!

37
00:12:26,868 --> 00:12:29,036
Thanks, lads.

38
00:15:42,165 --> 00:15:44,065
Much further?

39
00:15:45,068 --> 00:15:47,669
Much further, captain?

40
00:15:47,835 --> 00:15:50,806
I don't know.
I never used this road.

41
00:15:55,742 --> 00:15:58,746
Comrade junior lieutenant,
may I--?

42
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:12,591
Comrade junior lieutenant,
they're our fighter planes.

43
00:16:15,692 --> 00:16:17,526
I can see that myseIf!

44
00:16:18,528 --> 00:16:21,196
Comrade junior lieutenant,
