55
00:29:33,258 --> 00:29:38,230
This amuIet will heIp you fight
the weakness in your body.

56
00:29:45,835 --> 00:29:47,104
I have to....

57
00:29:47,269 --> 00:29:49,571
Don't be shy.

58
00:29:55,143 --> 00:29:57,244
Go on!

59
00:30:06,787 --> 00:30:10,290
You'll get better. Sleep.

60
00:34:43,151 --> 00:34:46,487
So, what are you going to
do now, lieutenant?

61
00:34:48,456 --> 00:34:51,125
I'll piss on your grave yet!

62
00:36:43,852 --> 00:36:47,621
Hello. I have to get the chain off.

63
00:36:47,788 --> 00:36:49,924
I need a blacksmith.

64
00:36:53,626 --> 00:36:57,430
Do you speak Finnish?
I want to get this off!

65
00:36:57,596 --> 00:36:59,566
Do you understand?

66
00:37:02,134 --> 00:37:07,238
You want the iron off?
You were a prisoner?

67
00:37:07,405 --> 00:37:13,143
I don't understand you. Do you
speak Finnish? You're a Lapp?

68
00:37:13,311 --> 00:37:16,812
I need a blacksmith. Is there a man?

69
00:37:16,979 --> 00:37:20,216
I need to get the chain off!

70
00:37:20,382 --> 00:37:23,619
I can't walk like this!

71
00:37:24,787 --> 00:37:29,457
You shout a lot.
Shouting never broke an iron.

72
00:37:31,391 --> 00:37:34,228
I'll have a look,
my husband had some tooIs.

73
00:37:35,995 --> 00:37:37,998
Anything you say, madam.

74
00:38:09,491 --> 00:38:11,726
Your husband?

75
00:38:12,726 --> 00:38:14,895
Sick?

76
00:38:17,030 --> 00:38:20,166
Is he your husband?

77
00:38:20,333 --> 00:38:22,100
Are you wounded or sick?

78
00:38:22,734 --> 00:38:25,403
Fritz. SS....

79
00:38:26,471 --> 00:38:28,139
Russian.

80
00:38:32,943 --> 00:38:38,248
