90
00:39:24,186 --> 00:39:25,820
Are you wounded?

91
00:39:26,822 --> 00:39:30,325
You were probably in that car.

92
00:39:31,359 --> 00:39:32,993
In the auto.

93
00:39:33,193 --> 00:39:34,528
Airplane.

94
00:39:36,696 --> 00:39:40,200
I couldn't understand why
the Russian planes fired at you.

95
00:39:43,703 --> 00:39:49,141
Shoot, you scum. My own people
will put me up against a wall, anyway.

96
00:39:49,307 --> 00:39:53,777
I'm Veikko. And you? Ivan?

97
00:39:53,945 --> 00:39:55,445
Get lost!

98
00:39:55,613 --> 00:39:57,848
Gerlost!

99
00:39:58,014 --> 00:40:01,584
Veikko, Gerlost.... And you?

100
00:40:01,750 --> 00:40:06,154
Anni. I just told you my reaI name!

101
00:40:06,321 --> 00:40:09,524
You can put the eye on me now.

102
00:40:10,057 --> 00:40:12,526
Anni, Gerlost, Veikko.

103
00:40:12,693 --> 00:40:14,095
A pleasure to meet you.

104
00:40:14,261 --> 00:40:18,732
It's a shame we haven't got
anything to ceIebrate with.

105
00:40:20,733 --> 00:40:24,669
Don't worry about me bIabbering.
It's the nerves.

106
00:40:24,836 --> 00:40:29,808
A condemned man that survived,
