107
00:40:31,609 --> 00:40:33,077
I see.

108
00:40:46,288 --> 00:40:49,391
I don't think they're pleased to see me.

109
00:40:49,558 --> 00:40:52,626
I'm sorry I've disturbed your peace.

110
00:40:52,793 --> 00:40:56,263
I'll take the chain off and go.

111
00:40:57,331 --> 00:41:01,333
Come on.
I'll give you the tooIs.

112
00:41:28,957 --> 00:41:31,326
These are my husband's tooIs.

113
00:41:35,595 --> 00:41:40,766
Your husband makes Lapland knives?

114
00:41:43,936 --> 00:41:46,438
You're a sharp Iad.

115
00:41:49,774 --> 00:41:52,777
Probably had to fight the girIs off.

116
00:41:54,945 --> 00:41:57,781
Or did you have a few?

117
00:41:58,782 --> 00:42:03,118
I'll take the chain off and go.

118
00:42:13,060 --> 00:42:15,329
It's my fourth year without a man.

119
00:42:15,496 --> 00:42:19,732
Last night I hugged the Russian.
He sIept...

120
00:42:19,900 --> 00:42:23,535
...but I was aching below the tummy.

121
00:42:29,807 --> 00:42:32,076
You smell bad.

122
00:42:32,243 --> 00:42:36,981
All men smell of iron and death now.

123
00:42:37,147 --> 00:42:38,682
Yes, lots of midges.

124
00:42:38,849 --> 00:42:41,684
When I was chained on the rock...

125
00:42:41,851 --> 00:42:44,186
...I thought they'd eat me away.

126
00:42:44,353 --> 00:42:48,089
Fortunately the wind bIew them off.

127
00:42:48,323 --> 00:42:53,395
Have you got a sauna?
Can I have a wash?

128
00:42:53,561 --> 00:42:56,964
Your skin's white,
whiter than any woman I've seen.

129
00:42:57,130 --> 00:43:04,270
The midges bit you because
you wash too often.

130
00:43:06,939 --> 00:43:10,709
Four years without a man,
and then two at once.

131
00:43:10,875 --> 00:43:13,577
Have the spirits read my thoughts?

132
00:43:21,751 --> 00:43:28,090
He's got my skirt on!
Why are you dressed like a woman?!

133
00:43:37,531 --> 00:43:43,569
Grinning, Fritz? Won't be
grinning for much longer!

134
00:43:57,248 --> 00:43:59,483
A good knife, but the handIe's short.

135
00:44:00,483 --> 00:44:03,453
Gerlost, I told you,
the war's over for me.

136
00:44:03,720 --> 00:44:08,524
I don't want to kill, but I don't
want to be killed. Understand?

137
00:44:08,691 --> 00:44:11,593
Go on, finish me off.

138
00:44:11,759 --> 00:44:16,062
That's my husband's knife.
It's mine when he's not here.

139
00:44:23,703 --> 00:44:27,572
Don't go killing each other!
I don't plan to bury you both.

140
00:44:28,573 --> 00:44:30,809
What are you waiting for?

141
00:44:31,776 --> 00:44:37,414
Think I'll kill you? My war is over,
my friend! Understand?

142
00:44:37,748 --> 00:44:40,316
Understand? My war is over.

143
00:44:41,317 --> 00:44:43,819
Leo ToIstoy, "War and Peace."

144
00:44:45,788 --> 00:44:49,023
Shoot, scum.

145
00:44:49,191 --> 00:44:54,762
Leo ToIstoy, "War and Peace."
Understand?

146
00:44:55,830 --> 00:44:59,833
I understand you're a fascist.
You burnt Yasnaya Polyana.

147
00:45:00,000 --> 00:45:05,504
I'm not a fascist. I'm a Finn.

148
00:45:05,672 --> 00:45:11,477
I was at university, then the war.
I didn't want to fight.

149
00:45:13,077 --> 00:45:16,447
You idiot! Fyodor Dostoyevsky.

150
00:45:16,613 --> 00:45:20,550
Fyodor Dostoyevsky. You idiot!

151
00:45:20,717 --> 00:45:23,452
I can't understand a word....

152
00:45:23,619 --> 00:45:26,656
I'm tired of fighting!

153
00:45:27,823 --> 00:45:34,462
Ernest Hemingway,
"A Farewell to Arms"!

154
00:45:36,864 --> 00:45:39,499
I don't know Russian.

155
00:45:40,868 --> 00:45:44,637
I should have studied it.
Sorry, Gerlost.

156
00:45:47,272 --> 00:45:49,608
It's abominabIe and miserabIe here.

157
00:45:52,877 --> 00:45:55,280
It's beautiful here.

158
00:45:55,579 --> 00:45:57,381
It was only yesterday...

159
00:45:57,548 --> 00:46:03,019
...when I was a condemned man,
chained to a rock like Prometheus.

160
00:46:03,186 --> 00:46:06,055
Just when I figured out
about Prometheus...

161
00:46:06,221 --> 00:46:10,860
...I thought about it further
and saw how to get the chain off.

162
00:46:11,392 --> 00:46:16,264
I could have used other means
instead of the glasses.

163
00:46:16,830 --> 00:46:21,834
They weren't as practicaI. I could've
taken the bullet out of the shell...

164
00:46:23,502 --> 00:46:29,174
...and shot in the grass.
It would have probably caught fire.

165
00:46:32,477 --> 00:46:37,215
I hope people will look back
in horror at what they did at war.

166
00:46:37,381 --> 00:46:42,753
The main thing is, we're alive.
You and me.

167
00:46:43,753 --> 00:46:47,590
Maybe they won't even
think about the whole thing.

168
00:46:50,526 --> 00:46:54,429
Man is capabIe of
doing strange things.

169
00:46:54,595 --> 00:46:57,064
Dostoyevsky said that.

170
00:47:01,834 --> 00:47:04,671
You can make a lot
of good things with it.

171
00:47:08,573 --> 00:47:10,276
He's cheered up, the fascist.

172
00:47:10,976 --> 00:47:13,778
I never shared the views
of the fascists. I'm a democrat.

173
00:47:15,046 --> 00:47:18,949
-Fascist, all the same.
-Democracy!

174
00:47:21,484 --> 00:47:25,555
Come and eat.

175
00:47:25,722 --> 00:47:28,691
Let's go and eat.

176
00:47:37,165 --> 00:47:44,504
Worried I'll thump you? I would,
if it weren't for the concussion.

177
00:47:45,505 --> 00:47:50,842
It's my second.
First was in the winter of '42.

178
00:48:02,118 --> 00:48:04,453
Can I have some more?

179
00:48:07,122 --> 00:48:13,228
You eat a lot. To eat a lot,
you have to work a lot.

180
00:48:13,394 --> 00:48:15,029
Thank you.

181
00:48:29,641 --> 00:48:32,645
Thank you,
everything was very tasty.

182
00:48:34,412 --> 00:48:38,916
Usually I don't drink coffee,
but thanks for that.

183
00:48:52,494 --> 00:48:54,495
Stupid woman.

184
00:49:13,478 --> 00:49:15,746
Got a smoke?

185
00:49:15,913 --> 00:49:17,549
Got a snout?

186
00:49:18,583 --> 00:49:21,818
<i>{y:i}Bitte, eine Zigarette.</i>

187
00:49:21,985 --> 00:49:25,788
If I had one, I'd smoke it myseIf.

188
00:49:27,623 --> 00:49:29,958
Thanks, fascist.

189
00:49:39,400 --> 00:49:44,070
Take it off, I'll wash it.

190
00:49:46,138 --> 00:49:52,378
Take that off as well.

191
00:49:55,146 --> 00:49:59,417
You just love wrapping
yourseIf up in clothes.

192
00:50:12,328 --> 00:50:16,664
You're not bad.
GirIs like your kind.

193
00:50:17,832 --> 00:50:19,601
Listen, Fritz!

194
00:50:20,000 --> 00:50:23,237
She seems to like you.

195
00:50:24,671 --> 00:50:29,442
What are you in a dress for?
Take it off. You look silly.

196
00:50:29,609 --> 00:50:31,343
Get lost!

197
00:50:31,510 --> 00:50:39,417
Gerlost, you're shy.
The Lapps don't understand that.

198
00:50:39,583 --> 00:50:43,052
They live a simple life.

199
00:50:43,220 --> 00:50:48,557
You talk a lot. My ears are ringing from
all those words. I don't understand it.

200
00:50:48,724 --> 00:50:53,863
She hasn't got much fish ready.
The winter will be hard.

201
00:50:54,029 --> 00:50:59,267
We're just extra mouths to feed.
We have to go quickly.

202
00:51:14,479 --> 00:51:16,615
My eyesight's fine.

203
