...so I started wearing glasses.

207
00:51:33,295 --> 00:51:36,030
I never thought they'd save me.

208
00:52:09,559 --> 00:52:12,161
She hasn't got much hay ready.

209
00:52:12,327 --> 00:52:16,832
Maybe just enough for the deer. They
can eat moss even under the snow.

210
00:52:17,699 --> 00:52:20,868
They should be
taken to their winter pastures.

211
00:52:21,135 --> 00:52:23,637
Yes, be off, chatterbox!

212
00:52:26,807 --> 00:52:28,574
Let me heIp!

213
00:52:28,742 --> 00:52:35,046
Don't come near me
or I'll get wet and want to shout!

214
00:52:40,818 --> 00:52:44,722
She's angry.
The girI's smitten.

215
00:52:45,322 --> 00:52:46,790
What?

216
00:52:47,156 --> 00:52:49,258
I said, she's smitten.

217
00:53:00,435 --> 00:53:02,636
I'm making a chimney for the sauna.

218
00:53:03,537 --> 00:53:05,372
I'm covering this with cIay.

219
